1
00:00:50,973 --> 00:00:52,892
Did you know that almost 4,000 people

2
00:00:52,892 --> 00:00:54,894
trip and fall worldwide every hour?

3
00:00:55,186 --> 00:00:55,770
Great.

4
00:00:55,770 --> 00:00:57,814
Another piece of useless info
taking up space in your brain.

5
00:00:57,814 --> 00:00:59,023
Congrats, man.

6
00:00:59,816 --> 00:01:02,721
Of all the people who could've
ended up in that statistic,

7
00:01:02,944 --> 00:01:04,237
why did it have
to be Kiko and me?

8
00:01:05,282 --> 00:01:08,360
And it happened during the most
cursed SDE shoot of our lives.

9
00:01:08,367 --> 00:01:09,403
You're probably not asking,

10
00:01:09,407 --> 00:01:10,827
but this is how it all started.

11
00:01:11,795 --> 00:01:12,799
Hey.

12
00:01:12,823 --> 00:01:13,967
Have you lost your mind?

13
00:01:13,991 --> 00:01:15,659
Why are you giving a monologue
when we're already late?

14
00:01:15,662 --> 00:01:16,915
You think you're
the main character?

15
00:01:26,295 --> 00:01:27,838
That event was something else.

16
00:01:27,838 --> 00:01:28,838
So exhausting.

17
00:01:29,215 --> 00:01:30,716
You know what took so long?

18
00:01:31,042 --> 00:01:32,626
The CEO's speech.

19
00:01:33,302 --> 00:01:34,696
Damn, it went on for an hour.

20
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:36,556
He just kept repeating
the exact same things.

21
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:42,937
Repeated it, but it was beautiful.

22
00:01:43,688 --> 00:01:45,132
Man, so many life lessons.

23
00:01:45,138 --> 00:01:46,148
Beautiful indeed.

24
00:01:46,149 --> 00:01:47,149
Yeah.

25
00:01:48,651 --> 00:01:49,793
Hey.

26
00:01:49,817 --> 00:01:51,193
Hey. What’s your problem?

27
00:01:51,485 --> 00:01:53,362
Well, bro, the boss texted.

28
00:01:54,488 --> 00:01:55,548
Probably about work.

29
00:01:55,572 --> 00:01:56,700
Then just long-press it to preview.

30
00:01:58,271 --> 00:01:59,620
But bro, it's a voice message.

31
00:02:00,625 --> 00:02:02,169
Let’s just pretend we fell asleep.

32
00:02:02,752 --> 00:02:04,355
But what if it's important?

33
00:02:04,379 --> 00:02:05,606
Let's just listen to it.

34
00:02:05,630 --> 00:02:06,756
Good evening, guys.

35
00:02:07,132 --> 00:02:08,758
It's me. Your boss.

36
00:02:09,505 --> 00:02:11,215
Who is also basically your family.

37
00:02:12,112 --> 00:02:13,405
Hope you guys are doing good.

38
00:02:14,156 --> 00:02:15,157
I'm doing okay.

39
00:02:15,699 --> 00:02:16,825
Just tired. Really tired.

40
00:02:17,772 --> 00:02:20,844
Struggling to find clients. Because...

41
00:02:20,870 --> 00:02:24,373
some other SDE creators
are accepting 5k packages.

42
00:02:24,915 --> 00:02:27,001
They're ruining our industry.

43
00:02:28,063 --> 00:02:29,086
Anyway,

44
00:02:29,337 --> 00:02:31,297
I just need to ask for a small favor.

45
00:02:32,006 --> 00:02:34,050
Someone needs to
cover a shoot tomorrow.

46
00:02:34,388 --> 00:02:36,306
One of the teams
had an emergency.

47
00:02:36,857 --> 00:02:39,234
There's really no one else
available but you two.

48
00:02:39,902 --> 00:02:40,902
Remember,

49
00:02:41,153 --> 00:02:44,948
the company's livelihood
depends on you.

50
00:02:45,574 --> 00:02:46,909
Our family's livelihood.

51
00:02:47,367 --> 00:02:49,453
One heart, one family.

52
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:51,288
Don't be late, okay?

53
00:02:51,663 --> 00:02:53,165
Call time is 4:00 AM.

54
00:02:53,540 --> 00:02:55,584
Love, your boss.

55
00:02:56,046 --> 00:02:57,149
Love you.

56
00:02:57,173 --> 00:02:58,233
Stay safe always.

57
00:02:58,252 --> 00:03:00,281
What the heck?
Look what time it is.

58
00:03:00,305 --> 00:03:01,765
Yeah, and call time is at 4:00 AM.

59
00:03:01,765 --> 00:03:02,765
Ouch.

60
00:03:02,772 --> 00:03:05,339
Alright, fine. Let’s pack up
so we can get some rest.

61
00:03:05,353 --> 00:03:07,312
It's all because of that
CEO's stupid speech.

62
00:03:08,272 --> 00:03:09,335
Exactly.

63
00:03:09,339 --> 00:03:10,963
It was so beautiful!

64
00:03:10,963 --> 00:03:13,131
- Hey, it really was beautiful.
- Man, that speech was incredible.

65
00:03:13,460 --> 00:03:14,961
Felt like Vin Diesel giving a speech.

66
00:03:14,961 --> 00:03:16,504
Best Speech Ever!

67
00:03:27,265 --> 00:03:29,142
You guys look absolutely exhausted.

68
00:03:29,434 --> 00:03:30,894
You're carrying so many cameras.

69
00:03:32,020 --> 00:03:33,605
And you just came
from an event, right?

70
00:03:34,272 --> 00:03:35,732
Is that what they call an SDE?

71
00:03:36,566 --> 00:03:37,901
Is that what you guys shoot?

72
00:03:39,444 --> 00:03:40,444
That’s right.

73
00:03:41,071 --> 00:03:43,490
Your job must be so exciting.

74
00:03:44,584 --> 00:03:45,979
Only at first, sir.

75
00:03:46,003 --> 00:03:48,186
There's no excitement
left in what we do.

76
00:03:48,189 --> 00:03:49,189
It’s just a routine now.

77
00:03:49,209 --> 00:03:51,771
At this point, I could probably
do it with my eyes closed.

78
00:03:51,795 --> 00:03:52,842
Really?

79
00:03:52,866 --> 00:03:54,798
So, how do you
actually make an SDE?

80
00:03:56,925 --> 00:03:57,925
Like this.

81
00:03:58,318 --> 00:04:02,587
First, you start with cinematic
shots of the event location.

82
00:04:02,598 --> 00:04:04,445
Using drones, obviously.
To make it aesthetic.

83
00:04:05,998 --> 00:04:09,102
And then, you can't forget—
you know,

84
00:04:09,126 --> 00:04:12,043
that perfect background music.

85
00:04:12,049 --> 00:04:15,440
Then you layer in a snippet
of the priest's homily.

86
00:04:15,464 --> 00:04:17,673
...and love one another.

87
00:04:18,621 --> 00:04:19,706
Awww!

88
00:04:20,161 --> 00:04:22,956
You can't miss the couple’s
gift exchange, either.

89
00:04:23,780 --> 00:04:25,247
Include the entourage, too,

90
00:04:25,574 --> 00:04:29,686
who are always so excited
about the gift-giving.

91
00:04:30,955 --> 00:04:33,375
Next up is the shot of
the bride’s entrance.

92
00:04:33,389 --> 00:04:34,460
The groom starts crying.

93
00:04:35,189 --> 00:04:36,902
It’s basically required
that he cries.

94
00:04:37,577 --> 00:04:39,821
The couple is having fun
with the wedding party,

95
00:04:39,824 --> 00:04:41,272
entering the reception,

96
00:04:41,591 --> 00:04:43,426
the first dance, blah blah blah,

97
00:04:43,426 --> 00:04:44,969
then we get paid.

98
00:04:47,889 --> 00:04:48,931
It’s always just like that.

99
00:04:49,223 --> 00:04:50,933
Over and over.
Pretty boring, right?

100
00:04:51,184 --> 00:04:52,560
But at least there are no hiccups.

101
00:04:52,810 --> 00:04:54,562
We’re just too good.

102
00:04:55,313 --> 00:04:57,023
Never a single mistake.

103
00:04:57,273 --> 00:04:58,273
But...

104
00:04:58,649 --> 00:04:59,776
it gets old.

105
00:05:01,027 --> 00:05:02,528
Anyway, man.
We’re gonna take a nap.

106
00:05:02,528 --> 00:05:03,529
You ask too much.

107
00:05:04,197 --> 00:05:05,197
Uh, sir...

108
00:05:05,441 --> 00:05:07,589
we’ve been here at your
destination for a while.

109
00:05:07,595 --> 00:05:08,805
About 30 minutes now.

110
00:05:09,366 --> 00:05:11,119
I didn't want to interrupt your story.

111
00:05:11,126 --> 00:05:12,126
It was good!

112
00:05:13,670 --> 00:05:15,213
[alarm ringing]

113
00:05:18,842 --> 00:05:19,842
Sir!

114
00:05:20,135 --> 00:05:21,135
Sir!

115
00:05:21,636 --> 00:05:22,636
Sir!

116
00:05:23,013 --> 00:05:24,013
SIR!

117
00:05:24,431 --> 00:05:25,431
SIR!

118
00:05:35,668 --> 00:05:37,086
Holy sh... Shoot!

119
00:05:37,087 --> 00:05:38,505
We’re the shooters, ma'am.

120
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:42,007
Hello, ma'am?

121
00:05:42,801 --> 00:05:44,219
Yes, ma’am.
We’re on our way right now.

122
00:05:45,255 --> 00:05:46,255
What?!

123
00:05:46,280 --> 00:05:47,280
What “happy ending”?

124
00:05:48,449 --> 00:05:49,784
You have the wrong number!

125
00:05:51,452 --> 00:05:52,954
Crazy. Happy ending?

126
00:05:54,727 --> 00:05:55,727
Ma'am?

127
00:05:55,935 --> 00:05:57,497
Oh, yes. We are so sorry.

128
00:05:57,522 --> 00:05:58,689
We’ll be there in 10 minutes.

129
00:05:58,689 --> 00:06:01,117
Sorry, we had some
trouble with the pickup.

130
00:06:01,123 --> 00:06:02,299
- Our driver is an idiot.
- Hey!

131
00:06:02,323 --> 00:06:03,404
Uh, but...

132
00:06:03,410 --> 00:06:04,949
he’s actually a really
good guy at heart,

133
00:06:04,950 --> 00:06:06,877
so he's still a five-star
driver to me, ma'am.

134
00:06:06,890 --> 00:06:08,306
Five stars for being an idiot, ma'am.

135
00:06:08,330 --> 00:06:09,915
And for having a good heart.

136
00:06:10,617 --> 00:06:12,535
Alright, ma'am.
We're almost there.

137
00:06:12,535 --> 00:06:14,287
Talk to you later.
Bye, ma'am.

138
00:06:16,122 --> 00:06:17,122
The heck was that?

139
00:06:18,549 --> 00:06:19,549
Uhm...

140
00:06:19,574 --> 00:06:20,574
Sir.

141
00:06:20,576 --> 00:06:22,495
Sorry about that.
My friend here is a comedian.

142
00:06:23,925 --> 00:06:24,925
What was that, sir?

143
00:06:24,926 --> 00:06:27,345
Oh. Nothing.
I just said we're almost there.

144
00:06:32,141 --> 00:06:33,141
Thanks, man.

145
00:06:35,061 --> 00:06:36,061
Your bag, bro.

146
00:06:36,312 --> 00:06:37,312
Yeah. Wait.

147
00:06:37,835 --> 00:06:38,836
I'll carry this.

148
00:06:39,428 --> 00:06:40,720
Hurry up. We're late.

149
00:06:44,433 --> 00:06:45,934
Is this the Pineda Events Place?

150
00:06:46,166 --> 00:06:47,376
Well, I don't know.

151
00:06:47,376 --> 00:06:48,376
I'm an idiot, right?

152
00:06:48,919 --> 00:06:51,588
See? You were picking a fight.

153
00:06:52,173 --> 00:06:53,967
Well, at least now we
know he really is an idiot

154
00:06:53,967 --> 00:06:55,385
and he doesn't have a good heart.

155
00:06:56,302 --> 00:06:57,804
This is the place.
It's a 15-minute walk.

156
00:06:58,304 --> 00:06:59,514
Come on. Let’s run for it.

157
00:06:59,514 --> 00:07:00,515
- 15 minutes?
- Let's go.

158
00:07:01,141 --> 00:07:02,141
Let's go.

159
00:07:09,272 --> 00:07:10,356
Hurry up. We're late.

160
00:07:10,356 --> 00:07:12,108
I'm trying. The road here is terrible.

161
00:07:13,898 --> 00:07:14,941
Check the instructions.

162
00:07:15,872 --> 00:07:17,308
We've gone way too far.

163
00:07:17,332 --> 00:07:19,042
Looks like it’s been 30 minutes.

164
00:07:21,445 --> 00:07:23,072
Let's just go home.
Son of a bitch.

165
00:07:23,980 --> 00:07:24,980
It's so hot.

166
00:07:26,826 --> 00:07:28,035
They probably didn't
have a big budget.

167
00:07:28,035 --> 00:07:29,824
Rent must be cheap out here.

168
00:07:32,911 --> 00:07:33,911
I'm so tired, man.

169
00:07:33,912 --> 00:07:35,664
What kind of shoes
is that, anyway?

170
00:07:35,678 --> 00:07:37,031
I'm only carrying the small one.

171
00:07:37,045 --> 00:07:38,171
- Is it here?
- No.

172
00:07:38,625 --> 00:07:39,793
- Wrong way, wrong way.
- This way.

173
00:07:45,674 --> 00:07:46,674
Oh, wow!

174
00:07:46,842 --> 00:07:49,695
Ma'am, your videographers
are finally here—

175
00:07:49,707 --> 00:07:51,162
guess they’re only filming
the reception now.

176
00:07:51,174 --> 00:07:52,174
What?

177
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:54,200
Just let it go. Let it slide.

178
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:55,596
Looks like he’s a
friend of the bride.

179
00:07:56,097 --> 00:07:57,787
Sorry, ma'am.
Don't worry, ma'am.

180
00:07:57,811 --> 00:07:59,490
We still have plenty
of time to shoot.

181
00:07:59,504 --> 00:08:01,762
Bro, get the lights.
Set this up.

182
00:08:01,762 --> 00:08:02,805
Let's show them what we've got.

183
00:08:02,805 --> 00:08:03,817
Let's show 'em.

184
00:08:03,824 --> 00:08:05,447
What took you so long?

185
00:08:05,457 --> 00:08:07,231
We've been waiting forever.

186
00:08:07,238 --> 00:08:08,340
Well, ma'am,

187
00:08:08,352 --> 00:08:10,758
the pin location you
sent us was wrong.

188
00:08:10,782 --> 00:08:13,076
- Yeah.
- I'm really sorry.

189
00:08:13,577 --> 00:08:15,329
It won't happen again.

190
00:08:15,913 --> 00:08:16,913
Hold on.

191
00:08:16,914 --> 00:08:19,266
Are you actually our videographers?

192
00:08:19,290 --> 00:08:20,977
I distinctly remember...

193
00:08:21,001 --> 00:08:22,336
they were supposed
to be two ugly guys.

194
00:08:22,753 --> 00:08:24,731
Ah, ma'am, we're the replacements.

195
00:08:24,755 --> 00:08:27,275
Since those two were ugly,
that means

196
00:08:27,286 --> 00:08:28,412
the two of us are the
handsome ones.

197
00:08:28,412 --> 00:08:29,514
Ah, no.

198
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:30,914
What I meant was,

199
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,702
now there's only one ugly guy.

200
00:08:32,726 --> 00:08:33,726
I see.

201
00:08:33,735 --> 00:08:35,129
Man, she says you're the ugly one.

202
00:08:35,141 --> 00:08:36,431
Yeah, I heard.

203
00:08:36,455 --> 00:08:37,455
Sorry about that.

204
00:08:37,461 --> 00:08:38,685
You’re so late. Hurry it up.

205
00:08:38,695 --> 00:08:39,695
- That's just how it goes.
- Come on.

206
00:08:39,701 --> 00:08:41,494
- One of us has to be the ugly one.
- Just hurry up.

207
00:08:43,502 --> 00:08:45,420
Okay, ma'am, just keep
doing what you're doing.

208
00:08:46,379 --> 00:08:47,672
I'm just shooting some BTS.

209
00:08:49,549 --> 00:08:50,967
You look so pretty, ma'am.

210
00:08:51,551 --> 00:08:52,969
That’s it. Just like that.

211
00:08:53,512 --> 00:08:54,679
Perfect, ma'am.
Just stay like that.

212
00:08:55,347 --> 00:08:56,973
That's it. So pretty.

213
00:08:57,641 --> 00:08:59,059
Okay, ma’am.
Give some emotion.

214
00:08:59,059 --> 00:09:00,560
You look beautiful.

215
00:09:00,977 --> 00:09:01,978
You look great right there.

216
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:03,403
- Oops.
- Ouch.

217
00:09:04,553 --> 00:09:05,553
Beautiful, ma'am.

218
00:09:06,233 --> 00:09:07,233
Right there, ma'am.

219
00:09:12,322 --> 00:09:14,032
Even here, seriously?

220
00:09:24,584 --> 00:09:25,585
This looks nice.

221
00:09:27,717 --> 00:09:29,218
Man, why don't you
just do it all?

222
00:09:30,017 --> 00:09:31,017
Take it.

223
00:09:31,578 --> 00:09:32,578
No, you do it.

224
00:09:32,598 --> 00:09:33,808
You’re being too much.

225
00:09:36,352 --> 00:09:37,562
There you go.

226
00:09:38,521 --> 00:09:41,065
Look at the handsome guy.

227
00:09:41,065 --> 00:09:43,025
Wow. Brand new, huh?

228
00:09:46,153 --> 00:09:47,363
Uh, ma'am...

229
00:09:48,030 --> 00:09:48,739
we're all done here.

230
00:09:48,739 --> 00:09:50,700
We're gonna head over
to the groom now.

231
00:09:53,369 --> 00:09:54,370
Hey, bro.

232
00:09:57,306 --> 00:09:59,517
Ouch. Oh.
[screams]

233
00:09:59,541 --> 00:10:01,358
What is wrong with you guys?
Be careful!

234
00:10:01,362 --> 00:10:02,405
We're so sorry, ma'am.
It's because...

235
00:10:02,429 --> 00:10:04,104
we were looking
at the handsome guy.

236
00:10:04,115 --> 00:10:05,271
Oh, uh...

237
00:10:05,275 --> 00:10:06,522
what I meant was...

238
00:10:06,529 --> 00:10:08,982
The handsome guy's tripod
was blocking the way.

239
00:10:09,535 --> 00:10:10,828
I'm really sorry.

240
00:10:11,373 --> 00:10:14,168
Good thing you guys
weren't the one who fell.

241
00:10:21,058 --> 00:10:22,058
Oh, finally!

242
00:10:23,686 --> 00:10:25,229
I thought you guys were
gonna scam us.

243
00:10:25,771 --> 00:10:27,774
- Uh.
- No, sir.

244
00:10:27,798 --> 00:10:29,550
Of course not.
We're not scammers.

245
00:10:29,983 --> 00:10:32,211
Actually, we're the best
in the industry.

246
00:10:32,216 --> 00:10:33,216
The best?

247
00:10:33,222 --> 00:10:35,599
But not the most punctual,
I guess.

248
00:10:36,529 --> 00:10:37,529
Yes.

249
00:10:37,536 --> 00:10:38,871
Actually, that's our motto.

250
00:10:39,538 --> 00:10:43,292
“The best, but not the
most punctual, I guess.”

251
00:10:43,626 --> 00:10:44,626
Yes, sir.

252
00:10:49,366 --> 00:10:50,366
Uhm..

253
00:10:50,646 --> 00:10:51,861
- Wait, sir.
- Bro.

254
00:10:51,866 --> 00:10:52,963
Yes? What?

255
00:10:55,486 --> 00:10:57,019
We're dead. Our battery is dead.

256
00:10:57,026 --> 00:10:59,114
I forgot to charge it after
yesterday's event.

257
00:11:00,491 --> 00:11:02,578
Go distract him for a bit
while I charge this here.

258
00:11:02,603 --> 00:11:03,603
Oh no.

259
00:11:03,619 --> 00:11:04,911
I didn't bring enough English for this.

260
00:11:04,911 --> 00:11:06,833
You can do it, otherwise
we won't get any footage.

261
00:11:07,199 --> 00:11:09,051
- Oh, great.
- Dammit. It didn't charge.

262
00:11:09,059 --> 00:11:10,159
Why now, of all times?

263
00:11:10,165 --> 00:11:11,202
Is there a problem?

264
00:11:11,470 --> 00:11:12,584
Oh!

265
00:11:12,609 --> 00:11:15,070
No, no, no.
Actually, we're very excited.

266
00:11:15,528 --> 00:11:16,821
And before we start,

267
00:11:17,072 --> 00:11:18,323
let me show you

268
00:11:18,703 --> 00:11:21,872
some photos of our latest client.

269
00:11:21,875 --> 00:11:22,875
- Okay.
- Okay.

270
