completely worthless!

802
00:35:16,803 --> 00:35:17,971
I'm just the editor here!

803
00:35:18,388 --> 00:35:20,514
Like my classmate back
in second grade said,

804
00:35:20,521 --> 00:35:22,016
I don't know how to do magic.

805
00:35:22,433 --> 00:35:23,768
I'm not a magician!

806
00:35:25,522 --> 00:35:26,522
I'm done, man.

807
00:35:26,536 --> 00:35:28,045
This really isn't for me.

808
00:35:28,056 --> 00:35:29,307
Hey, where are you going, bro?

809
00:35:29,682 --> 00:35:30,682
I'm leaving.

810
00:35:31,142 --> 00:35:33,394
Hey. Why? Are you some rich kid?

811
00:35:33,394 --> 00:35:34,394
No. Why?

812
00:35:35,271 --> 00:35:37,541
Because you're acting
like you're some rich kid.

813
00:35:37,565 --> 00:35:38,565
Hey!

814
00:35:38,575 --> 00:35:39,901
- I said no.
- Fucking coward.

815
00:35:40,409 --> 00:35:41,743
What? Who's a coward?

816
00:35:43,203 --> 00:35:44,204
Why are you leaving?

817
00:35:44,663 --> 00:35:48,250
The way you're acting,
you'd think you're some rich kid.

818
00:35:49,336 --> 00:35:50,712
The problem with you is,

819
00:35:51,130 --> 00:35:53,090
the moment things
don't go your way,

820
00:35:53,090 --> 00:35:54,383
you want to quit immediately.

821
00:35:55,217 --> 00:35:56,969
What are you? A billionaire?

822
00:35:58,595 --> 00:36:00,264
You think you're the only
one who wants to quit?

823
00:36:00,806 --> 00:36:02,558
I want to quit too, you know.

824
00:36:03,642 --> 00:36:04,725
But look at my situation.

825
00:36:05,352 --> 00:36:07,020
My wife just gave birth,

826
00:36:07,020 --> 00:36:08,856
and I owe a massive
debt to the bank.

827
00:36:10,941 --> 00:36:12,025
You think you're the only
one with dreams?

828
00:36:12,025 --> 00:36:14,153
I have dreams too, of course!

829
00:36:15,028 --> 00:36:17,156
But right now, reality demands

830
00:36:17,156 --> 00:36:20,868
that I prioritize my
family's needs first.

831
00:36:23,370 --> 00:36:25,038
Sure, what we do is repetitive.

832
00:36:25,038 --> 00:36:27,708
But to our clients,
it's a first-time experience.

833
00:36:28,375 --> 00:36:29,710
Especially for the newlyweds.

834
00:36:30,419 --> 00:36:31,545
It's their first time getting married.

835
00:36:31,545 --> 00:36:34,131
This might be the only wedding
they'll ever experience in their lives.

836
00:36:34,131 --> 00:36:37,217
That's why the shots we give them
are so important to them.

837
00:36:37,801 --> 00:36:41,388
We need to capture all
those beautiful memories

838
00:36:41,388 --> 00:36:43,098
because it's all for them.

839
00:36:48,270 --> 00:36:49,270
You're right, man.

840
00:36:52,482 --> 00:36:53,859
Whoa, what are you doing?

841
00:36:54,818 --> 00:36:56,445
I'm just saying you're right.

842
00:36:57,070 --> 00:36:58,322
I'm not gonna kiss you.

843
00:36:58,614 --> 00:37:00,073
No. I just fell asleep.

844
00:37:00,552 --> 00:37:01,552
As if.

845
00:37:02,284 --> 00:37:03,577
What are you trying to say?

846
00:37:05,581 --> 00:37:07,291
I just want to say that...

847
00:37:07,941 --> 00:37:08,941
you're right, bro.

848
00:37:09,567 --> 00:37:11,361
We can still save this day.

849
00:37:11,361 --> 00:37:12,963
People are counting on us.

850
00:37:12,987 --> 00:37:14,072
Right?

851
00:37:14,274 --> 00:37:15,274
- Game!
- Game.

852
00:37:15,280 --> 00:37:16,280
Okay.

853
00:37:16,287 --> 00:37:17,287
- Come on.
- Let's go.

854
00:38:23,649 --> 00:38:25,276
The video is absolutely hideous.

855
00:38:29,030 --> 00:38:31,407
What if I just don't
show up for a week?

856
00:38:33,534 --> 00:38:35,369
Should we just let boss's
anger hit the roof?

857
00:38:36,120 --> 00:38:38,983
Since he's going to be furious
about this terrible SDE anyway,

858
00:38:39,915 --> 00:38:41,083
let's just make a run for it.

859
00:38:41,083 --> 00:38:44,378
Better than embarrassing
ourselves to everyone.

860
00:38:44,378 --> 00:38:45,713
What about the
remaining balance?

861
00:38:47,423 --> 00:38:48,549
Well...

862
00:38:49,550 --> 00:38:50,550
Forget about that.

863
00:38:51,218 --> 00:38:53,095
Do you really think
they'll still pay us in full

864
00:38:53,095 --> 00:38:55,222
once they see how
awful the SDE is?

865
00:38:58,934 --> 00:38:59,934
Let's get out of here.

866
00:39:00,186 --> 00:39:01,186
Let’s go.

867
00:39:11,113 --> 00:39:12,113
Sigh.

868
00:39:12,846 --> 00:39:14,890
Why are we even
still doing this?

869
00:39:17,893 --> 00:39:20,771
To capture our clients'
memories, remember?

870
00:39:20,771 --> 00:39:23,273
I just gave a whole long
monologue about this earlier.

871
00:39:24,149 --> 00:39:25,149
I get it.

872
00:39:25,692 --> 00:39:26,777
I totally get it.

873
00:39:26,777 --> 00:39:28,945
Maybe today really
was just a bad day.

874
00:39:28,945 --> 00:39:30,530
We'll just make up
for it tomorrow.

875
00:39:31,842 --> 00:39:34,469
Exactly.
Like Albert Einstein said,

876
00:39:34,834 --> 00:39:38,153
"It's just a bad day,
not a bad life."

877
00:39:38,155 --> 00:39:39,155
He said that?

878
00:39:39,169 --> 00:39:40,795
Yeah. I saw it on social media.

879
00:39:40,795 --> 00:39:42,464
If it's on social media,
it must be true.

880
00:39:51,973 --> 00:39:52,973
Yes?

881
00:39:53,193 --> 00:39:54,847
Hello, ma'am?
We're so sorry,

882
00:39:54,857 --> 00:39:55,889
but we already left ahead.

883
00:39:55,889 --> 00:39:58,392
We have a really early
call time tomorrow.

884
00:39:58,934 --> 00:39:59,934
Is there a problem?

885
00:40:04,439 --> 00:40:06,483
Oh, you're welcome, ma'am!

886
00:40:08,652 --> 00:40:10,153
Thank you.
Thank you as well.

887
00:40:10,153 --> 00:40:11,154
Thank you so much.

888
00:40:13,115 --> 00:40:14,115
What did she say?

889
00:40:14,616 --> 00:40:16,868
She said she really
loved our shots.

890
00:40:17,536 --> 00:40:19,830
She said our approach
was unique and very artistic.

891
00:40:20,080 --> 00:40:22,749
The foreigner even said it felt
like a whole new film style,

892
00:40:22,749 --> 00:40:24,084
a new genre.

893
00:40:25,460 --> 00:40:26,460
Holy shit.

894
00:40:28,130 --> 00:40:29,381
They even asked for
our contact info,

895
00:40:29,381 --> 00:40:32,050
and she told us to upload
the SDE as soon as possible

896
00:40:32,050 --> 00:40:33,677
because they want
to watch it again.

897
00:40:35,137 --> 00:40:37,389
- We did it, man.
- That's great.

898
00:40:37,848 --> 00:40:39,141
[both] Whoo!

899
00:40:41,184 --> 00:40:42,436
That's awesome.

900
00:40:43,728 --> 00:40:45,981
Why do we keep grinding
so hard in life anyway?

901
00:40:46,338 --> 00:40:47,964
What is it that we get up
for every morning?

902
00:40:48,525 --> 00:40:51,153
And why is this scene starting to
feel like a coffee commercial?

903
00:40:51,605 --> 00:40:52,647
Just kidding...

904
00:40:53,023 --> 00:40:54,524
Why do we really do this?

905
00:40:55,150 --> 00:40:57,944
I guess it's to capture
our clients' memories.

906
00:40:57,944 --> 00:40:59,654
That's definitely a big part of it.

907
00:41:00,458 --> 00:41:03,336
But for me, we also do this for them.

908
00:41:03,878 --> 00:41:07,256
For the moments we get to capture
every single day alongside them.

909
00:41:07,798 --> 00:41:11,052
The very people who are right there
with you while you chase your dreams.

910
00:41:12,220 --> 00:41:13,221
Hi, babe!

911
00:41:15,244 --> 00:41:18,205
Yeah, we don't even know
how we survived this day.

912
00:41:18,747 --> 00:41:20,082
So much stuff happened.

913
00:41:20,082 --> 00:41:21,292
But somehow,

914
00:41:22,042 --> 00:41:23,377
the Lord helped us through.

915
00:41:26,839 --> 00:41:27,839
Wait, what?!

916
00:41:31,677 --> 00:41:33,220
- Hello?
- Hello, bro.

917
00:41:34,717 --> 00:41:37,220
The wedding we're supposed
to work on is actually tomorrow.

918
00:41:37,970 --> 00:41:38,970
What?

919
00:41:39,138 --> 00:41:41,265
Then whose wedding did
we just cover earlier?

920
00:41:41,604 --> 00:41:41,931
Son of a—

921
00:41:42,140 --> 00:41:42,964
Wow.

922
00:41:43,266 --> 00:41:44,476
Amazing.

923
00:41:44,757 --> 00:41:46,467
What a wonderful gift.

924
00:41:46,800 --> 00:41:48,511
I am very surprised.

925
00:41:48,511 --> 00:41:48,924
Wah.

926
00:42:01,607 --> 00:42:02,149
Bro.

927
00:42:02,399 --> 00:42:04,485
When is our shoot again?

928
00:42:04,818 --> 00:42:06,612
The one at Pineda's Place?

929
00:42:07,029 --> 00:42:09,615
The one those two ugly
guys passed off to us.

930
00:42:10,282 --> 00:42:11,492
That's on Thursday, right?

931
00:42:11,992 --> 00:42:13,911
Dude, it was Thursday yesterday.

932
00:42:14,411 --> 00:42:15,955
Thursday is tomorrow!

933
00:42:16,789 --> 00:42:18,999
Dude, today is Friday!

934
00:42:19,886 --> 00:42:20,886
Son of a bitch!
